  "body": "### Description\nI will attach the graph \n<img width=\"1905\" src=\"https://api.zenhub.com/attachedFiles/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBMFg1QWc9PSIsImV4cCI6bnVsbCwicHVyIjoiYmxvYl9pZCJ9fQ==--df94fb67538b87f10ed73900f97d2ab28a6e568b/image.png\" alt=\"image.png\" />\n\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\n1. Start a node using Jenkins using besu_download_url: https://output.circle-artifacts.com/output/job/47cc784b-6347-4f41-a1bf-b5e3fb0eab89/artifacts/0/distributions/besu-24.1.1-SNAPSHOT.tar.gz\n(rest is default, use any network, like holesky, goerli, etc) \n2. Wait until intial sync has finished\n\n**Expected behavior:** number of peers stays stable when sync finishes\n\n**Actual behavior:** we are loosing up to 60 of our existing peers\n\n**Frequency:** we are loosing at least some peers, visible in Grafana\n\n\n",
